<doc id="186549" wikidata="Q5769980" url="?curid=186549" title="Hiroo Yamagata">
<text>is a Japanese author, critic, economist and translator. He translated some works in computer technology such as &quot;The Cathedral and the Bazaar&quot; by Eric S. Raymond, &quot;Code and Other Laws of Cyberspace&quot; by Lawrence Lessig into Japanese. 

He is the founder and chairman of Project Sugita Genpaku, which is a volunteer effort to translate free content texts into Japanese.

